	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=120740><span id=Scholar>ayere</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>27 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You misread my post. Enchanters are clearly on my &quot;leave alone&quot; list :)&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Inexperienced Pallys usually forget about LoH until it's too late, so they usually die with a well timed HT. An experienced PvP'er, reguardless of class will beat an inexperienced one. An experienced PvP SK *should* beat an equally competent Paladin given the abilities available. LoH against HT may seem like a win for the Paladin, however, the SK just has more offensive capability. Lifetap seems to tip the balance in favor of the SK as it does the double duty of both healing and causing damage to the opponent.<br><br>And yes, any Necro who duels without SS and Enstill (against melee) deserves his fate. At the higher levels a 49 or 56 Necro pet can not exactly be ignored - they have substantial tanking ability. One or two 50+ level dot's also do enough damage to kill a SK quickly.<br><br>Here's the reason I respect the Necro in PvP situations more than others. When I hit 52 with my SK, I considered myself a decent PvP'er. I'd racked up my share of Ranger, Paladin, Warrior, Monk and even an insane Cleric kills. Even took me down a Wizard once. Then one time, this Necro 2 levels lower than me was standing alone in the Arena without a pet. He owned me. I thought I was doing well, I'd ran to him a couple times between his Shadow Steps and managed to get him to about 60% health, it looked like I was still full. Then, he managed to SS and hide. He sat there hidden somewhere while my life clicked away. I died, logged and started a Necro. But that's just me, I may suck.<br><br>By the way, as a Necro I've killed a bunch of Pally's. They are easier to kill than SK's. :-) My Necro leaves Enchanters and Bards alone. Mage's put up a good fight until their pet dies. Rangers are tough, probably even with SK's (don't get near that blender lol). All others are do-able without too much trouble.<br><br>I apologize if this post wastes too much time. Just relaying my own personal experiences. Your mileage may vary. :)<br><br>Dyre, 53 SK</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
